        <desc id="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01" dbi="ltsept1800.1.1.LT">
            <objtitle>
                <title type="transcribed">I cannot immediately determine whether</title>, <objid>
                    <objnumber code="A1">Object 1 </objnumber>
                </objid>
            </objtitle>
            <physdesc desclevel="brief">
                <objsize>23.6 x 20.3 cm.</objsize>
                <objnote>
                    <p>The full sheet was folded to form two leaves. Butts's letter
                        appears on the first recto (Object 1), first verso (Object 2), second recto 
                        (Object 3), and second verso (Object 4). This folded sheet was folded further 
                        to form a sealed letter packet.</p>
                    <p>The number "2" is inscribed in the upper right corner in an unknown hand.</p>
                </objnote>
                <windowsize width="840" height="1050"/>
            </physdesc>
            <phystext>
                <lg justify="left">
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.01" justify="left" indent="28">Marlborough Street</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.02" justify="left" indent="5">Dear Sir,</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.03" justify="left" indent="14">I cannot immediately determine whether</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.04" justify="left">or no I am dignified by the Title you have graciously</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.05" justify="left">conferred on me &#8212; you cannot but recollect the difficulties</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.06" justify="left" indent="40"><substSpan spanto="B1"/><add type="insertions" place="supralinear">discerning clearly</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.07" justify="left">that have unceasingly arisen to prevent my <del type="overstrike">reading</del><anchor xml:id="B1"/> whether</l> 
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.08" justify="left">your Angels are black white or <choice><orig>grey</orig><reg>gray</reg></choice> <del type="overstrike"><choice><orig>altho</orig><reg>although</reg></choice></del> and that <del type="overstrike">I</del></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.09" justify="left" indent="4"><substSpan spanto="B2"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">on the whole I have</add><space extent="2"/><gap extent="6" reason="cancellation" unit="character"/></l>                                                       
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.10" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">have</del><anchor xml:id="B2"/> of the three rather inclined to the former opinion and</l>                                                       
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.11" justify="left" indent="15"><subst><add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret">^</add></subst></l>                                                                                                               
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.12" justify="left">considered. you more immediately under the protection of</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.13" justify="left">the <choice><orig>black-guard</orig><reg>blackguard</reg></choice> however at any rate I should thank you</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.14" justify="left" indent="18"><substSpan spanto="B3"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">to</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.15" justify="left">for an introduction <del type="overstrike">at</del><anchor xml:id="B3"/> his <choice><orig>Highnesss</orig><reg>Highness's</reg></choice> Court that when<note>Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1543) reads "to" for "at".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.16" justify="left">refused admittance into other Mansions I may not be</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.17" justify="left"><substSpan spanto="B4"/><add type="insertions" place="supralinear">received as</add><space extent="10"/><gap extent="1" reason="cancellation" unit="character"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.18" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">taken as</del> a Stranger in<del type="overstrike">t</del><anchor xml:id="B4"/> this
                                                                <note>Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1543) reads "stranger" for "Stranger; Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1543) reads "His for "this".</note></l> 
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.19" justify="left" indent="15">I am well pleased with your pleasures feeling</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.20" justify="left">no small interest in your Happiness and it cannot fail to</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.21" justify="left">be highly gratifying to me and my affectionate Partner to</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.22" justify="left">know that a Corner of your Mansion of Peace is <choice><orig>asylumd</orig><reg>asylumed</reg></choice> to<note>Keynes (*Letters*, page 25) reads "asylumed" for "asylumd".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.23" justify="left" indent="45"><substSpan spanto="B5"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">who shall</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.24" justify="left">Her &#38; when invalided &#38; rendered unfit for service <del type="overstrike">it is not</del><anchor xml:id="B5"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.25" justify="left" indent="2"><substSpan spanto="B6"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">say</add><space extent="14"/><add type="insertion" pace="supralinear">not</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.26" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">unforseeable</del> she may <del type="overstrike">take a take</del><anchor xml:id="B6"/> be <choice><orig>quarterd</orig><reg>quartered</reg></choice>' on your Cot.&#8212;</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.27" justify="left" indent="20"><subst><add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret">^</add></subst><space extent="11"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">active</add><space extent="4"/><subst><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">satisfied with</add></subst></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.28" justify="left">but for the present she is <gap reason="cancellation" extent="4" unit="character"/> <del type="overstrike">f</del><gap reason="cancellation" extent="2"/> for Duty and <gap extent="4" reason="cancellation" unit="character"/> requesting</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.29" justify="left" indent="13"><subst><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">Snug Berth</add></subst><space extent="11"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear" symbol="caret">^</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.30" justify="left">that if there is a <subst><del type="overstrike">Corner</del></subst> unoccupied in any Chamber of your</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.31" justify="left" indent="42"><substSpan spanto="B8"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">there at the same time</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.32" justify="left">warm Heart that her Portrait may be <del type="overstrike">there</del><anchor xml:id="B8"/> suspended well aware</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.01.33" justify="left" indent="48"><subst><add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret">^</add></subst></l>
                    </lg>
            </phystext>
        </desc>
        <desc id="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02" dbi="ltsept1800.1.2.LT">
            <objtitle>
                <title type="editorial">cont.</title>, <objid>
                        <objnumber code="A2">Object 2 </objnumber>
                    </objid>
            </objtitle>
            <physdesc desclevel="brief">
                <objsize>23.6 x 20.3 cm.</objsize>
                <objnote>
                    <p>The full sheet was folded to form two leaves. Butts's letter
                        appears on the first recto (Object 1), first verso (Object 2), second recto 
                        (Object 3), and second verso (Object 4). This folded sheet was folded further 
                        to form a sealed letter packet.</p>
                </objnote>
                <windowsize width="840" height="1050"/>
            </physdesc>
            <phystext>
                <lg justify="left">
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.01" justify="left">that you like me prefer the Original to the Copy&#8212;Your</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.02" justify="left">good Wife <gap extent="1" reason="cancellation"/> will permit &#38; I hope may benefit from the Embraces</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.03" justify="left" indent="24"><subst><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">presently</add></subst></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.04" justify="left" indent="20"><substSpan spanto="C1"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">she will <gap extent="3" reason="cancellation"/> distinguish betwixt the warmth of his &#38;</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.05" justify="left">Embraces of Neptune but <del type="overstrike">she will they</del> <gap extent="25" reason="cancellation"/><anchor xml:id="C1"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.06" justify="left" indent="39"><subst><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">former</add></subst></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.07" justify="left" indent="28"><substSpan spanto="C2"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">&#38; court the</add><del type="overstrike">m</del> <add type="insertion" place="supralinear">with caution I suppose</add>
                                                                <note>Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1543) reads this passage as 
                                                                "Your good Wife will permit &#38; I hope may benefit from the Embraces of Neptune but she will presently distinguish betwixt 
                                                                the warmth of his Embraces, &#38; yours, &#38; court the former with caution"; Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1543) notes that an earlier draft of this sentence reads as follows: 
                                                                "'but they must be courted with far more caution than yours . . . recollecting that what may be taken by all must be prejudicial to some'".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.08" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">far more caution th</del> and yours <gap extent="35" reason="cancellation"/><anchor xml:id="C2"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.09" justify="left"><substSpan spanto="C3"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">you do not admit of a third in that concern</add> <del type="overstrike">there</del><space extent="5"/> <add type="insertion" place="supralinear">even</add> </l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.10" justify="left" indent="12"><subst><del type="overstrike">as common another Partner</del></subst> <add type="insertion" place="supralinear">or I would offer her mine at this distance &#35;</add><note>The symbol at the end of line 10 seems to indicate that lines 9-11 on Object 4 marked by the same symbol are intended for insertion here.</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.11" justify="left" indent="27"><add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret">^</add> <subst><del type="overstrike">may</del></subst><space extent="18"/> <add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret">^</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.12" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">that what may be taken by all must be prejudicial to some</del><anchor xml:id="C3"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.13" justify="left" indent="53"><substSpan spanto="C4"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">virtuous</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.14" justify="left">who alass! of us my good Friend could have thought that so <del type="overstrike">good</del><anchor xml:id="C4"/> a woman would ever have <del type="overstrike"><choice><orig>barterd</orig><reg>bartered</reg></choice></del>
                                                                <note>Keynes (*Letters*, page 25) reads "alas" for "alass".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.15" justify="left"><substSpan spanto="B9"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">exchanged</add><space extent="23"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">Buildings</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.16" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">exchanged the Buildings of</del><anchor xml:id="B9"/> Hercules for <del type="overstrike">the Bed of</del> Neptunes? Bed?<note>Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1544) transcribes this passage as a verse couplet ("So Virtuous a Woman would ever have fled, / From Hercules' Buildings to Neptunes Bed") and notes that they were first expressed as prose. Keynes (*Letters*, page 25-26) includes the deleted or overwritten portions of text here so that "so good a Woman would ever have exchanged Hercules Buildings for Neptune's Bed," precedes the verse couplet.</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.17" justify="left" indent="24">Whether you will be a better Painter or a better</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.18" justify="left" indent="9"><substSpan spanto="B10"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">your</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.19" justify="left">Poet from <del type="overstrike">the</del><anchor xml:id="B10"/> change of ways &#38; means I know not; but this</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.20" justify="left">I predict, that you will be a better Man &#8212; excuse me, as you<note>Bentley (*Writings* volume 2, page 1544) reads "Excuse" for "excuse".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.21" justify="left">have been accustomed from friendship to do, but certain opinions</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.22" justify="left" indent="35"><subst><add type="insertion" place="supralinear"><choice><orig>nourishd</orig><reg>nourished</reg></choice></add></subst></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.23" justify="left">imbibed <del type="overstrike">from indulgence</del> from reading <substSpan spanto="B11"/><del type="overstrike">rivitted</del> by indulgence, <note>Keynes (*Letters*, page 26) reads "rivetted" for "rivitted".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.24" justify="left" indent="38"><add type="insertion" place="inline">^</add><anchor xml:id="B11"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.25" justify="left">and rivitted by a confined Conversation, and which have been</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.26" justify="left" indent="46"><substSpan spanto="B12"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">now, I trust,</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.27" justify="left">equally prejudicial to your Interest &#38; Happiness, will, <del type="overstrike">gradually</del><anchor xml:id="B12"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.28" justify="left" indent="18"><substSpan spanto="B13"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear"><choice><orig>Day break</orig><reg>Daybreak</reg></choice> <choice><orig>Vapour</orig><reg>Vapor</reg></choice>,</add><space extent="6"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">henceforth</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.29" justify="left">disperse <del type="overstrike">before</del> as a <del type="overstrike">Memory</del><anchor xml:id="B13"/><gap reason="cancellation" extent="5"/>and you will become a</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.30" justify="left" indent="17"><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">, in the opinion of the Archbishop of Canterbury,</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.31" justify="left">Member of that Community of which you are at present <add type="insertion" place="inline"><hi rend="subscript">^</hi></add> but</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.32" justify="left" indent="24"><substSpan spanto="B14"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">residence of</add><space extent="8"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">dim</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.33" justify="left">a <choice><orig>Sign-</orig><reg>Signpost</reg></choice><del type="overstrike">post</del> to mark the <del type="overstrike">Bend that leads to where</del><anchor xml:id="B14"/> incredulity,</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.34" justify="left" indent="38"><substSpan spanto="B15"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">can be effected by sterling</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.35" justify="left">haggard suspicion, &#38; bloated philosophy <del type="overstrike">reside</del> &#8212; whatever <add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret"><hi rend="subscript">^</hi></add> <del type="overstrike">good</del><anchor xml:id="B15"/>Sense
                                                                <note>Keynes (*Letters*, page 26) reads "sense" for "Sense".</note></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.36" justify="left">by opinions which <choice><orig>harmonize</orig><reg>harmonise</reg></choice> <del type="overstrike">with</del> society and beautify creation</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.37" justify="left" indent="12"><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">, in future</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.38" justify="left"><del type="overstrike">can effect</del> will <add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret"><hi rend="subscript">^</hi></add> be exemplified in you &#38; the time I trust is</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.39" justify="left">not distant and that because I truly regard you when you</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.40" justify="left" indent="7"><substSpan spanto="B16"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">more</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.41" justify="left">will be a<del type="overstrike">s</del><anchor xml:id="B16"/> valorous <del type="overstrike">a</del> Champion of Revelation &#38; Humiliation</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.42" justify="left"><substSpan spanto="B17"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">than</add><space extent="2"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">of those</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.43" justify="left"><subst><del type="overstrike">as</del></subst> any who now wield the Sword of the Spirit <gap extent="2" reason="cancellation"/> with your</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.44" justify="left" indent="1"><add type="insertion" place="inline">^</add><space extent="4"/><add type="insertion" place="inline">^</add><anchor xml:id="B17"/></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.45" justify="left">natural &#38; acquired Powers <del type="overstrike">to a much better effect</del> nothing</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.46" justify="left" indent="53"><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">both</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.47" justify="left">is wanting but a proper direction of them &#38; <choice><orig>altho</orig><reg>although</reg></choice> the way is <add type="insertion" place="inline" symbol="caret"><hi rend="subscript">^</hi></add> straight</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.48" justify="left">&#38; narrow I know you too well to fear your want of resolution</l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.49" justify="left" indent="17"><substSpan spanto="B18"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">&#38; to</add><space extent="28"/><add type="insertion" place="supralinear">Plough</add></l>
                    <l n="ltsept1800.1.ltr.02.50" justify="left">to <gap extent="5" reason="cancellation"/> persevere <del type="overstrike">in</del><anchor xml:id="B18"/> <choice><orig>pursu</orig><reg>pursue</reg></choice><subst><del type="overstrike">it</del><add type="overwrite" place="inline">e</add></subst> <del type="overstrike">of</del> it &#8212; you have the <subst><del type="overstrike">Harrow</del></subst> &#38; the</l>
                </lg>
            </phystext>
        </desc>
        <desc id="ltsept1800.1.ltr.03" dbi="ltsept1800.1.3.LT">
            <objtitle>
                <title type="editorial">cont.</title>, <objid>
                    <objnumber code="A3">Object 3 </objnumber>
                </objid>
            </objtitle>
            <physdesc desclevel="brief">
                <objsize>23.6 x 20.3 cm.</objsize>
                <objnote>
